CriteriaParameter.Name: plain.categorylesionstate.definition
CriteriaParameter.Value:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?> <!-- Lesionstate definition for mint Lesion version 3.2 Copyright 2014 Mint Medical GmbH --> <MintLesionStates xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" ApplicationVersion="3.2"> <!-- \warning: If this document is changed during development, it's content needs to be written to the criteria property '<criteria_id>.lesionstate.definition' in all SQLScripts! --> <!-- xsi:schemaLocation="LesionAnalyzer/Modules/AssessmentCriteria/LesionStatesRules/ressources/LesionStateSchema_Manual.xsd" --> <Criteria> <AvailableCategories> <!-- All available categories should be listed here with: - MappedObjectCategory (integer): Used to map category to mitk::ObjectCategory::ECategory enum - ID: String ID of lesion state - DisplayNameSingular: Singlular display string of category - DisplayNamePlural: Singlular display string of category - Code: Category code used for lesion ID (e.g. T01)
e.g. <Category MappedObjectCategory="2" ID="Finding" DisplayNameSingular="Finding" DisplayNamePlural="Findings" Code="F" />
Note: Restriction for MappedObjectCategory is the size of mitk::ObjectCategory::ECategory enum list. --> <Category MappedObjectCategory="2" ID="Finding" DisplayNameSingular="Finding" DisplayNamePlural="Findings" Code="F" /> </AvailableCategories> <AvailableLesionStates> <!-- All available lesion states should be listed here with: - MappedLesionStateIndex (integer): Used to store and map the lesion state definition in the XML definition - ID: String ID of lesion state - DisplayName: Display string of lesion state
e.g. <Category MappedObjectCategory="2" ID="Finding" DisplayNameSingular="Finding" DisplayNamePlural="Findings" Code="F" />
Note: Restriction for MappedLesionStateIndex is the size of mitk::ObjectCategory::ECatory enum list. --> <LesionState MappedLesionStateIndex="0" ID="LESION_UNDEFINED" DisplayName="Undefined" /> <LesionState MappedLesionStateIndex="1" ID="LESION_NOTASSESSED" DisplayName="Not assessed" /> <LesionState MappedLesionStateIndex="2" ID="LESION_NOTEVALUABLE" DisplayName="Not evaluable" /> <LesionState MappedLesionStateIndex="3" ID="LESION_DISAPPEARED" DisplayName="Disappeared" /> <LesionState MappedLesionStateIndex="4" ID="LESION_REGRESSION" DisplayName="Regressive" /> <LesionState MappedLesionStateIndex="5" ID="LESION_PRESENT" DisplayName="Present" /> <LesionState MappedLesionStateIndex="6" ID="LESION_PROGRESSION" DisplayName="Progressive" /> <LesionState MappedLesionStateIndex="7" ID="LESION_NEW" DisplayName="New" /> </AvailableLesionStates> <!-- For each row in the lesion state table, copy the corresponding <LesionStatesRules> tag and fill in the condition values. Then set the resulting lesion states by deleting surplus states and promote one to the default state by changing the <State> tag to <DefaultState>
The LesionCategory has to be available in the list of <Categories> with the same ID.
All lesion states have to be available in the list of <AvailableLesionStates> with the same ID. -->
<!-- Finding: Definition 1 --> <LesionStatesRules LesionCategory="Finding"> <hasPreviousObservation Value="false" /> <readingDefined Value="false" /> <isBaselineObservation Value="any" /> <ValidStates> <DefaultState ID="LESION_UNDEFINED" /> </ValidStates> </LesionStatesRules>
<!-- Finding: Definition 2 --> <LesionStatesRules LesionCategory="Finding"> <hasPreviousObservation Value="false" /> <readingDefined Value="true" /> <isBaselineObservation Value="false" /> <ValidStates> <DefaultState ID="LESION_NEW" /> </ValidStates> </LesionStatesRules>
<!-- Finding: Definition 3 --> <LesionStatesRules LesionCategory="Finding"> <hasPreviousObservation Value="false" /> <readingDefined Value="true" /> <isBaselineObservation Value="true" /> <ValidStates> <DefaultState ID="LESION_PRESENT" /> </ValidStates> </LesionStatesRules>
<!-- Finding: Definition 4 --> <LesionStatesRules LesionCategory="Finding"> <hasPreviousObservation Value="true" /> <readingDefined Value="false" /> <isBaselineObservation Value="any" /> <ValidStates> <DefaultState ID="LESION_NOTASSESSED" /> <State ID="LESION_NOTEVALUABLE" /> <State ID="LESION_DISAPPEARED" /> </ValidStates> </LesionStatesRules>
<!-- Finding: Definition 5 --> <LesionStatesRules LesionCategory="Finding"> <hasPreviousObservation Value="true" /> <readingDefined Value="true" /> <isBaselineObservation Value="any" /> <ValidStates> <DefaultState ID="LESION_PRESENT" /> <State ID="LESION_DISAPPEARED" /> <State ID="LESION_REGRESSION" /> <State ID="LESION_PROGRESSION" /> </ValidStates> </LesionStatesRules> </Criteria> </MintLesionStates>
